# Testing Protocol

Before completing ANY code change in this project, you MUST:

1. Run the full test suite with `python -m pytest --tb=short -q`
2. If any test fails, fix the issue before presenting the solution
3. If you added new functionality, add corresponding tests in `tests/`
4. If you modified existing functionality, verify existing tests still pass

## Running Tests

```bash
python -m pytest --tb=short -q
```

## Test Structure

- `tests/unit/` — Unit tests (pure logic, no I/O, fast)
- `tests/integration/` — Integration tests (DB, API endpoints)
- `tests/fixtures/` — Sample data files (RSS XML, etc.)
- `tests/conftest.py` — Shared fixtures (`make_article`, `sample_articles`, `sample_groups`, `temp_db`)

## Rules

- Never skip or delete failing tests to make CI pass
- Always add tests for new features or bug fixes
- Keep test data in `tests/conftest.py` or `tests/fixtures/`
- Integration tests that need DB must use the `temp_db` fixture
